1. install git

- Linux 
  "yum install git"
  "pacman -S git"
  "apt-get install git"

- Windows: 

  install "Git-1.7.11-preview20120620.exe";
  Set the "PATH" environment variable, by putting "C:\Program Files (x86)\Git\bin" in the *front* of the list. This is to ensure we use the right "find.exe", not the one comes with Windows. To do so, go the steps similar to the following: Control Panel->System->Advanced settings->Environment Variable...
  

2. Clone the depot:

- goto a directory desired
- do: git clone https://xiongyw@github.com/xiongyw/xiongyw.git
  or using ssh: git clone git@github.com:xiongyw/xiongyw.git

3. Config

git config --local user.name "Yuwu Xiong"
git config --local user.email "xiongyw@hotmail.com"
git config --local alias.st status
git config --local alias.ci commit
git config --local alias.co checkout
git config --local alias.br branch
git config --local color.ui true
git config --local fileMode false


4. Changing from HTTPS to SSH access:

- generate ssh key, upload pub key into github and test it
https://help.github.com/articles/generating-ssh-keys

ssh -T git@github.com

- change the remote url
https://help.github.com/articles/changing-a-remote-s-url

git remote -v
git remote set-url origin git@github.com:xiongyw/xiongyw.git

5. tag

- create: git tag <yyyymmdd>
- delete: git tag -d <yyyymmdd>
- list all: git tag #
- push: git push origin --tags
- delete from remote: git push --delete origin <the_tag>

6. tutorial:

http://lostechies.com/joshuaflanagan/2010/09/03/use-gitk-to-understand-git/
